A common, basic VHS VCR can be used as a low noise analog recorder. I supplied a crystal microphone and audio pre-amplifier and fed this into the &#39;audio in&#39; on the VCR. Playback can be monitored on a TV set or the audio out can be fed to a computer. I post processed in ClearVoice to remove a slight 60hz hum and reduce the high frequencies. Background sound was provided by a high speed manual sweep tune of an FM broadcast radio. Here&#39;s a couple of the best so far.

&quot;Time for amazing voices&quot;

This was a reverse playback capture &quot;Hey David.....I&#39;m grounded&quot;

Thanks for listening,
Dave
